<HEADLINE> Li Ruihuan Visits Exhibition on Beijing's Urban Planning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Visiting an exhibition on
urban planning of Beijing today, senior Chinese leader Li Ruihuan
said that urban planning is of great importance and needs
intensified management.
</P>
<P>
Li, chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference, made detailed inquiries about
the construction of road, water, natural gas and subway facilities
in the Chinese capital city.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan, also member of the Standing Committee of the
Political Bureau of the Chinese Communist Party Central Committee,
said the population and land use in Beijing must be put under strict
control and can not be expanded at will.
</P>
<P>
Accompanied by Jia Qinglin, mayor of Beijing and other local
officials, Li noted that the city's downtown area must be
protected well, and the density and height of buildings must be
limited. 
</P>
</TEXT>
