<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Hire Zambian Air Traffic Controllers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe has brought in an
unknown number of air traffic controllers from neighboring Zambia
to salvage the critical situation in the country's air travel
industry following last week's dismissal of 67 local controllers.
</P>
<P>
The Zimbabwe News Agency reported that the Zambian air traffic
controllers were today being trained to acquaint them with the
Zimbabwean air space.
</P>
<P>
The Department of Civil Aviation of Zimbabwe confirmed the
arrival of the Zambian delegation but did not give further
details.
</P>
<P>
The Zimbabwean government suspended and subsequently dismissed
air traffic controllers who went on strike demanding increasing
salaries and improved working conditions.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Zimbabwe's two main airlines confirmed on Tuesday
all flights are back to normal and travel will continue as
scheduled. 
</P>
</TEXT>
