<HEADLINE> Angolan President Accepts Invitation to Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Angolan President Eduardo dos
Santos today accepted the invitation from Chinese President Jiang
Zemin to visit China.
</P>
<P>
During his talks with Chinese ambassador to Angola Xiao Sijin
who conveyed the invitation on behalf of President Jiang, dos
Santos expressed his thanks to the Chinese president for the
invitation and accepted it in pleasure.
</P>
<P>
The Angolan president praised the Chinese government for its
support to the Angolan people in their struggle against
colonialism and for national independence in the past. Relations
between Angola and China have been promoted by joint efforts in
recent years and the prospect for bilateral trade and economic
cooperation is broad and bright, he added.
</P>
<P>
Angola should learn from China which has achieved great
progress since it adopted a reform and opening-up policy and also
accumulated rich experience in national construction, he noted.
</P>
<P>
The Angolan president said that China is playing a
positive role in international affairs, including African and
southern African affairs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
