<DOCNO> XIE19971231.0016 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France Condemns Latest Violence in Algeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 30 (Xinhua) -- France today condemned the
latest violence in Algeria on the eve of the Muslim fasting month
of Ramadan, which has killed at least 80 people over the past
three days.
</P>
<P>
"One cannot but condemn the violence which the (Algerian)
press has reported," said French Foreign Ministry spokesman Yves
Doutriaux.
</P>
<P>
About 300 people have been killed over the past 10 days, most
of them in the western part of Algeria, assumably by Islamic
militants. 
</P>
</TEXT>
