<HEADLINE> Mozambique Slashes Toll of International Phone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
According to the new rates announced by the Mozambican
Telecommunications Corporation (TDM), phone calls to Mozambque's
nine neighboring countries, including South Africa, Zambia and
others, will now cost 8,600 Meticais (about 0.74 U.S. dollars),
per minute, starting from January 1 next year.
</P>
<P>
Phone calls to Angola, Cape Verde, Sao Tome and Principe,
Kenya and Uganda will now cost 16,200 Meticais per minute, while those to
Europe, Asia, America, Latin American and other parts of Africa
will cost 28,800 Meticais per minute.
</P>
<P>
This is the second time in this year that Mozambique has
reduced the charge for international phone calls.  
</P>
