<HEADLINE> Greece, Albania Sign Cooperation Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Greece and Albania today signed
a cooperation agreement following talks between Greek Transport
and Communications Minister Tassos Mandelis and his visiting
Albanian counterpart Gaqo Apostoli.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, which was signed by the two ministers, the
two countries will cooperate in road, passenger and goods
transportation.
</P>
<P>
Greece agreed to assist Albania technically in the organization
and operation of long-distance and urban transport, the
manufacture and operation of airports and heliports as well as the
training of coach drivers and air traffic controllers, the
semi-official Athens News Agency (ANA) reported today.
</P>
<P>
The two countries decided that conveyance of goods between them
and the transit of goods should be allowed to proceed freely
without any quantitative restrictions.
</P>
<P>
They also agreed that Albania should become part of the inter-
European road network. 
</P>
