<HEADLINE> UK Cargo Ship Sinks in Atlantic off Florida </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 30 (Xinhua) -- A British-owned cargo ship
began sinking in rough seas in the Atlantic Ocean this morning and
U.S. Coast Guard helicopters were rescuing the 28 crew members
from the churning waters.
</P>
<P>
The 493-foot (160-meter) Merchant Patriot was 270 miles (435
km) east of Cape Canaveral, Florida. The ship, which was traveling
from Praia Mole, Brazil, to Savannah, Georgia, began sinking after
a water pipe ruptured in the engine room and flooded the vessel,
reports from Miami said.
</P>
<P>
Five U.S. Air Force and Coast Guard helicopters from bases in
Florida and the Bahamas joined the rescue task. The rescued
crewmen were being flown to Marsh Harbor on Great Abaco Island,
Bahamas.
</P>
<P>
Strong wind blew away the life raft on the ship and the crewmen
have to leap into the water one by one to let the helicopters pick
them up.
</P>
<P>
The vessel is owned by the British company Cenergo Navigation
Ltd. and was flying a Ukrainian flag. 
</P>
