<HEADLINE> Britain Pledges to Make Single Currency Success </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 31 (Xinhua) -- British Foreign Secretary Robin
Cook pledged here today that Britain would use its coming European
Union (EU) Presidency to make the single European currency a
success.
</P>
<P>
Cook told BBC Radio this afternoon that the Labor government,
due to take over the EU presidency on Thursday, would make sure
the European Monetary Union (EMU) proceed properly although London
will not join the single currency in the first wave.
</P>
<P>
"What we are going to do is make sure that the plans for the
single currency are sensibly carried out and everything possible
is done to make sure that those who want to go ahead succeed,"
Cook said.
</P>
<P>
Cook emphasized the importance of the single currency to
British economy by saying "Remember our own economy is very
heavily bound up in the continent."
</P>
<P>
"It is most certainly not in Britain's interests that this
project should go ahead and not prove a success," he added.
</P>
