<HEADLINE> U.S. First-time Unemployment Claims Pick Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 31 (Xinhua) -- The United States received
13,000 more first-time claims for unemployment benefits during
the Christmas week than the week before, the Labor Department
reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The unemployment benefit applications totaled 318,000 last
week, up from 305,000 the week before.
</P>
<P>
Despite the increase, the unemployment rate in November stood
at 4.6 percent, still the lowest in 24 years.
</P>
<P>
The strong labor market has boosted consumer confidence to the
highest level in 28 years, according to surveys yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Claims have fluctuated in a range between 304,000 and 322,000
for the past six weeks. A four-week moving average of initial
claims, which smoothes weekly fluctuations, edged down by 1,000 to
314,250. 
</P>
</TEXT>
