<HEADLINE> Business at Hongqiao Airport in Shanghai Booming in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Hongqiao International
Airport handled a record of 13.2 million passengers this year.
</P>
<P>
The 1997 numbers up to today are 112,000 flights and 470,000
tons of goods and luggage, a rise of 10.71 percent and 15.2
percent, respectively, over 1996.
</P>
<P>
Forty-two domestic and overseas airline companies have opened
more than 300 air routes linking Shanghai with 97 cities both at
home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
One of the busiest airports in China, Hongqiao has experienced
a sharp increase of handling volumes in the past decade, along
with the rapid economic development of the metropolis.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the airport has invested 47 million yuan (5.6
million U.S. dollars) in advanced facilities to guarantee
transportation safety, such as radio alarms and communication
systems, flight information networks, X-ray testing devices and
detectors. 
</P>
