<HEADLINE> Zambian Siamese Twins Successfully Separated in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Zambian Siamese twins
were successfully separated in a 20-hour operation ended this
morning at a hospital near Pretoria, the South African Press
Association reported.
</P>
<P>
The two boys, Luka and Joseph Banda, were joined at the top of
their heads.
</P>
