<HEADLINE> People's Daily Editorial Marks New Year (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 31 (Xinhua) -- The Thursday edition of
People's Daily, China's leading newspaper, will carry an editorial
marking the beginning of 1998.
</P>
<P>
The editorial -- "March forward triumphantly under the
guidelines of the 15th National Congress of the Communist Party of
China (CPC)" -- notes that 1998, the year of tiger according to
the Chinese lunar calendar, will be a year filled with vigor and
hope for China.
</P>
<P>
The editorial points to 1997 as "a year of many joyful harvests
in various aspects and a year of great historical significance".
</P>
<P>
According to the editorial, "In 1997, the Party Central
Committee with Comrade Jiang Zemin at the core carried forward the
behest of Comrade Deng Xiaoping, and scored remarkable successes in
leading the whole Party and people of all ethnic groups across the
nation on an unswerving march forward along the path of building
socialism with Chinese characteristics."
</P>
<P>
In 1997, Chinese people also witnessed the complete success of
two major events -- the return of Hong Kong to the motherland on
July 1, and the convening of the 15th CPC National Congress in
September in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The editorial points out that steady national economic progress
has further enhanced the nation's economic strength and this has
led to continuous improvement of the life of the Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
"While many countries throughout the world have been affected
by the recent global financial crisis, our country's financial
sector and overall economy have maintained stability."
</P>
<P>
The editorial also points out that exciting breakthroughs in
China's foreign affairs have helped further improve the country's
image and status in the global community.
</P>
</TEXT>
