<P>
"Our Party and nation have achieved a great historic turn
during the past two decades, and have opened a new era of reform
and opening," it adds.
</P>
<P>
The editorial notes that it is critically important to carry on
and further develop the fine traditions of the Party which were
restored by the Plenum, as well as the good style of work formed
in the new period.
</P>
<P>
"We must conscientiously adhere to the ideological line
of 'emancipating the mind' and 'seeking truth from facts', the
very essence of Deng Xiaoping Theory," the editorial stresses.
</P>
<P>
Only by emancipating their minds and seeking truth from facts,
can people remove the restraints of various unrealistic and
outdated concepts and, in turn, usher in a new situation for
China's socialist modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
"The 15th National Party Congress represented a new milestone
in our Party's efforts to emancipate the mind and seek truth from
facts," it continues.
</P>
<P>
The editorial says that "We can surely achieve greater success
in various undertakings after we grasp the full essence of the
congress."
</P>
</TEXT>
