<HEADLINE> Premier Li Peng Inspects Power Plant in West Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng
inspected Shijingshan General Power Plant on the western outskirts
of Beijing on the last day of 1997, extending greetings to workers
and learning about the plant's working conditions.
</P>
<P>
Heads of the power plant explained electricity and heating
functions to the premier, who was accompanied by Jia Qinglin,
Beijing Mayor and secretary of the Beijing Municipal Committee of
the Communist Party of China.
</P>
<P>
Li praised power plant workers for their contribution to
China's capital and its residents and urged them to make greater
achievements in ensuring the success of Beijing's reform,
development and stability.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Premier also visited families of two retired
workers.
</P>
<P>
Established in 1919, the plant has become the major electrical
and heating supplier of Beijing, generating 4.5 billion
kilowatts-hour annually and providing heating to units and
households that cover a total floor space of more than eight
million square meters. The plant has an installed generating
capacity of more than 1.16 million kilowatts. 
</P>
