<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-31 12:47 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Oil, Gas Reserves Found in Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Iran has found new reserves of
1.49 billion barrels of oil, 31.85 trillion cubic feet of gas and
596 million barrels of liquid gas in the current Iranian year
ending on March 20, 1998, an Iranian official said today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to Iran's official news agency IRNA, exploration
director of the National Iranian Oil Company (NIOC) Mahmoud
Mohaddes said that the new oil and gas reserves were discovered in
the Persian Gulf as well as in the southern provinces of
Khuzestan, Fars and Bushehr.
</P>
<P>
It is expected that with the drilling of about 300 wells, some
18 trillion to 200 trillion cubic feet of gas and over 15 billion
barrels of oil will be discovered in other fields, he said.
</P>
<P>
Mohaddes said that exploitation operations in subterranean
surfaces of Bibi Kakimeh field in southern Iran are indicative of
1.984 trillion cubic feet of gas reserves.
</P>
<P>
He said that Zagros area has the largest gas potentials in the
country, especially the region between Aghar and Dalan gas fields
stretching toward Bandar Abbas and the strait of Hormuz.
</P>
<P>
Earlier reports said that the country has an oil reserve of
about 93 billion barrels, ranking fourth in the world, and a gas
reserve of 742.3 trillion cubic feet, ranking the second in the
world. It is believed that Iran will find new oil and gas reserves
with the exploration in the Caspian Sea region.
</P>
<P>
At present, Iran's oil output stands at 3.6 million barrels
per day (bpd) and the figure will be raised to about 4 million bpd
according to a decision of the Organization of Petroleum
Exporting Countries (OPEC). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
