<HEADLINE> Russia's Foreign Trade Up in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MOSCOW, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Russia's total foreign trade
volume increased by two percent in 1997 to 136 billion U.S
dollars, Russian Minister of Economic Relations and Trade said
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference, Mikhail Fradkov said Russia's export
decreased while import increased in 1997. But the country still
enjoyed a favorable trade balance of 3.6 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
He said Russia will promote export of machinery in the
future. It will also try to attract more investment in developing
enterprise specializing in making goods for export.
</P>
<P>
The official added Russia will reconstruct some of its overseas
business offices in 1998. 
</P>
