<HEADLINE> China Urges Fair Play in Mobile Phone Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 31 (Xinhua) -- China's mobile
telecommunications businesses and their sales agents are required
to clearly list mobile phone subscription fees and charges, fees
for roaming services, and prices for mobile phones.
</P>
<P>
China's State Economic and Trade Commission and Ministry of
Posts and Telecommunications jointly issued a notice calling on
related businesses to strictly abide by the regulations.
</P>
<P>
The notice stipulated that subscription fees for mobile phone
services can range from a minimum 1,000 yuan to a maximum
3,000 yuan, down from the previous 2,000-3,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Violations of pricing regulations, including unclear pricing,
any form of subscription fee reduction, sales of mobile phones
at below cost, and either over or undercharging for
service fees will be subject to severe penalties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
