<HEADLINE> Uganda Improves Fish Export Facilities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Uganda is installing a large
cold-storage facility near the Entebbe International Airport to
save its fish exports, a local report said.
</P>
<P>
The Uganda fish exporting companies said they were pressing
for the speeding up of the project to complete the storage
facility, ahead of the February 1998 European Union deadline on
its fish exports.
</P>
<P>
The European Union has threatened to ban all Uganda fish
exports, complaining they were of poor quality, being short of
storage facilities.
</P>
<P>
Fish is one of Uganda's key exports. Up to 20,000 tons are
exported out of more than 200,000 tons caught annually. The
country earns around 40 million U.S. Dollars per year from fish
exports.
</P>
<P>
Officials from the trade and industry ministry say they want
to make fish exports number two to coffee as a hard currency
earner. Coffee brings in up to 400 million U.S. Dollars each
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
