<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Rules for Securities Investment Advisers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 31 (Xinhua) -- China has unveiled a set of
provisions governing the securities consulting sector.
</P>
<P>
The regulations, which outline detailed qualification criteria
for consultants and related agencies, ban investment consultants
from investing in securities.
</P>
<P>
The provisions are designed to standardize consulting practices
related to securities and futures investments, protect individual
investors, and promote the standardized and sound development of
China's securities market, according to a spokesman for the
China Securities Regulatory Commission (CSRC).
</P>
<P>
The regulations will also be conducive to the self-development
of the securities consulting sector, according to the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
He also pointed out that numerous irregularities in the sector
resulting from low-level professionalism, the lack of
self-discipline, ignorance of professional ethics and weak
supervision have severely misled individual investors involved in
securities trading.
</P>
<P>
Individual investors, who still account for the major portion
of investments in China's securities sector, rely heavily on
professional advice. Therefore, the regulations represent a highly
significant measure adopted to standardize the market, according
to the spokesman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
