of securing the headquarters of the U.N. force and logistic support
to their colleagues from Nepal, Fiji, Finland, Italy, Ghana, Norway,
Ireland and Poland.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. force has been deployed in southern Lebanon since 1978,
in the wake of an Israeli invasion, to help the Lebanese
legitimate authorities control their territory ``up to the
internationally recognized frontier.''
</P>
