<HEADLINE> Share Prices Rally on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Share prices rallied on the
Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials Index
picked up by 15.01 points to close the year higher at 1529.84
points on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that share prices finished mostly higher largely
on year-end window dressing, though the trading session was
shortened ahead of Thursday's New Year holiday.
</P>
<P>
Selected foreign tranches of blue chip stocks were among the
biggest price gainers, thank to a last-minute buying spree, they
added.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume was thin at 122.83 million units,
valued at 171.79 million Singapore dollars (102.87 million U.S.
dollars). Advances led declines by 188 to 149, while 272 other
counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
MBf Capital was the most actively traded counter as it
registered a turnover of 15.17 million units. It was followed by
RHB Capital Warrant99 which had 7.36 million units traded. IOI
Corporation was next with 4.02 million of its shares changed
hands.
</P>
<P>
Local computer sound card maker Creative 50 led the gainers of
the day as it rose by 1.5 dollars to finish at 34.2 Singapore
dollars. NatBroad increased by 56 cents to end at 1.49 U.S.
dollars, while Asean Fund picked up by 50 cents to close at 7.5
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Sea View was the biggest loser as it declined
by 50 cents to end at six Singapore dollars. The Singapore Press
Holdings (SPH) Foreign fell by 40 cents to close at 21.1 Singapore
dollars. Jurong Engineering Warrant0207 was 25 cents lower at 45
Singapore cents.  
