<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiangsu Emerging as Leader in Information Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, December 31 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangsu Province
is expected to build a series of advanced information and
communication facilities and become a national leader in the
sector by 2010.
</P>
<P>
A high-speed optical fiber cable network will cover the whole
province and the information system will also be used in the
fields of government offices, public welfare, agriculture,
industry, trade, finance, social security and education.
</P>
<P>
The information industry should become a pillar in the
province's economy, according to the information industry plan
made public recently by the local government.
</P>
<P>
And 25 percent of the province's total population will receive
training on computer use and information technology.
</P>
<P>
While encouraging foreign investors to take part in the
construction, the province has worked hard to introduce advanced
technologies and expertise.
</P>
<P>
So far, the province has 10 million telephones, ranking second
in the country. About 87.5 percent of the province's population
can listen to broadcasts, and 94.5 percent can watch TV.
</P>
<P>
The electronics industry's annual industrial output exceeds 70
billion yuan (8.9 billion U.S. dollars). In the last five years
the province has developed more than 3,900 electronics projects at
a cost of 4 billion yuan (500 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
To date, several thousand people are engaged in developing
computer software. 
</P>
</TEXT>
