<HEADLINE> Jiang Delivers New Year's Message on State Radio and TV (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 31 (Xinhua) -- In a new year's message
broadcast worldwide today, President Jiang Zemin said that people
of all countries across the world should make joint efforts to
usher in a new century of enduring peace and common development.
</P>
<P>
In his message to the audience of China Central People's
Broadcasting Station, China Radio International and China Central
Television, delivered here on the eve of 1998, Jiang expressed his
confidence in the future of China and the world by titling the
message "March toward a promising new century."
</P>
<P>
Describing 1997 as "a very important and very extraordinary
year in the Chinese history," President Jiang said that the
Chinese people are determined to carry forward the behest of Deng
Xiaoping, who passed away in February in Beijing, and promote the
advancement of the cause of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, he recalled, the Chinese government smoothly resumed
its exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong and maintained Hong
Kong's prosperity and stability under the principle of "one
country, two systems," "Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong" and
a high degree of autonomy.
</P>
<P>
"Also this year, the Communist Party of China (CPC)
successfully convened its 15th National Congress, which, holding
high the great banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory, summarized China's
history over the past century and worked out the program for
action for the country's development in the next century," he
added.
</P>
<P>
He noted that China's reform, opening-up and modernization
drive continued to make progress in the past year, with high
growth and low inflation for the national economy, another bumper
harvest in agriculture, further deepening of enterprise reforms
and further improvement of people's lives.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, China's foreign economic and technological
cooperation and exchanges have continued to expand, while new
achievements have been scored in building democracy and the legal
system, promoting ethical and cultural progress and other social
undertakings, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
