<HEADLINE> Jiang Delivers New Year's Message on State Radio and TV (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Though we still face many difficulties in economic growth and
social progress, we surely can overcome them and continue to make
steady progress, for we have the guidance of Deng Xiaoping Theory,
rich experience accumulated in the past nearly two decades of
reform and opening-up, and many other advantages," he said.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang then acknowledged that it is the common
aspiration of all Chinese across the world to realize the complete
reunification of China.
</P>
<P>
"I believe that Macao will certainly return to the motherland
smoothly in December of 1999 with the cooperation and joint
efforts between China and Portugal," he said.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated that Taiwan is an inalienable part of China, and
that any attempt to create "two Chinas" or "one China, one Taiwan"
and seek "Taiwan independence" are doomed to fail.
</P>
<P>
