<HEADLINE> URGENT: Tarar Wins Pak Presidential Election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Senator Rafiq Tarar,
official presidential nominee of the ruling Pakistan Muslim League
(N) won the presidential election Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The final results are not available yet. According to earlier
results released by the Election Commission, Tarar was enjoying a
comfortable lead in the polling by securing 243 votes out of a
total of 298 votes in the National Assembly.
</P>
<P>
Shahban Mirani, the nominee of the major opposition Pakistan
People's Party, won seven votes. Out of the total 298 votes in the
National Assembly, seven votes declared invalid.
</P>
<P>
The total electoral college votes are 476, including 87
Senators, 217 members of the National Assembly and 43 votes of
each of the four provincial assemblies.
</P>
<P>
A candidate must poll at least 51 percent of the total or 239
votes to win the election.  
</P>
