<HEADLINE> Organizers of 1999 Junior World Cup Asked to Change Date </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, December 31 (Xinhua) -- New Zealand organizers of
the 1999 junior World Cup finals have been asked by the world
soccer governing body FIFA to put it off to October from January,
they said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The International Football Confederation (FIFA) wanted the move
to enable European and American countries to complete their
qualifying rounds during their traditional playing period from
April to May.
</P>
<P>
The Soccer New Zealand board will discuss the time change and a
decision is expected in the next couple of weeks, the organizers
said. 
</P>
