<HEADLINE> Two Claim Seeing Fiat After Accident Which Kills Diana </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Two people have reportedly
claimed seeing a Fiat coming out of the tunnel of Alma in Paris on
August 31, seconds after the crash which killed Princess Diana.
</P>
<P>
The two anonymous people -- one man and one woman -- said the
white Fiat Uno was driven by a European man of some 40 years old
with brown hair, said the daily Aujourd'hui/Parisien Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Fiat driver had a big dog at the back seat, they were
quoted as saying by a report in the daily newspaper. And his
behavior "appeared abnormal," as his car zigzagged.
</P>
<P>
The daily also cited an unpublished investigation report by
French investigators working on the case, which said the testimony
of the double witness was corroborated by scientific experts.
</P>
<P>
These presumed findings would "strengthen the hypothesis that
Diana's Mercedes car collided with a white Fiat Uno under the Alma
tunnel," the paper said. 
</P>
