<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, December 31 (Xinhua) -- The Yellow River Mechanical and
Electrical Co. Ltd in Xi'an, capital of northwest China's Shaanxi
Province, has begun mass production of multi-media TV sets, and
its first batch of such products is expected to be put into the
market soon.
</P>
<P>
The first generation of China's multi-media TV sets was developed
by the corporation, local research institutes and
universities. Besides operating as an ordinary TV set, the TV's
kinescope can be used as the monitor of a computer.
</P>
<P>
The picture quality and clarity of the multi-media TV sets is
better than the ordinary ones, and its cost has been greatly
reduced.
</P>
<P>
The corporation developed the first multi-media TV set last July,
and it has become the first enterprise in China for mass
production of the multi-media TV sets.  
