<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT December 31 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- A secret ballot poll to elect the ninth president
of Pakistan started Wednesday at 10.00 a.m. local time.
</P>
<P>
According to the Election Commission, the total electoral
college votes are 476, including 87 Senators, 217 members of the
National Assembly and 43 votes of each of the four provincial
assemblies. A candidate must poll at least 51 percent of the total
or 239 votes to win. (Pakistan-Presidential Election)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BANGKOK -- Thailand is expected to record zero economic growth
for 1997 and the prospects for recovery next year are uncertain,
according to a year-end report of the Bank of Thailand.
</P>
<P>
All the key economic indicators showed signs of slowdown since
the beginning of 1997 as a result of the financial crisis,
according to the report available Wednesday.
(Thailand-Economy-Zero Growth)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russia and Japan reached a draft agreement Tuesday on
fishing off the disputed Kuril islands, after three years of talks.
</P>
<P>
Russian chief negotiator Vasily Saplin said the two sides
agreed on quotas for Japanese fishermen, types of catches and time
limits for fishing.
</P>
<P>
He said that the agreement was expected to be signed by the two
governments in January 1998. (Russia-Japan-Fishery)
</P>
<P>
