<HEADLINE> Spark Program Advances Economic Growth in Chinese Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, December 31 (Xinhua) -- The Spark Program is expected
to produce an output value of 24.5 billion yuan (three billion US
dollars) in Shandong Province, east China, this year.
</P>
<P>
The province has so far built nearly 3,000 Spark Program projects,
361 of which are launched this year, with a total investment of
3.78 billion yuan and an estimated tax revenue of 4.35 billion
yuan.
</P>
<P>
The province has set up 18 technology-intensive regions and
spent 800,000 yuan setting up training centers, where 300,000
people have been trained.
</P>
<P>
Thirtyfour farmers in the province have been sent to Japan to
study.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Shandong has trained 1,800 people into vegetable
cultivation technicians for other Chinese provinces.
</P>
<P>
The Spark Program is designed to disseminate applicable
techniques in rural China to help farmers develop economy.
</P>
</TEXT>
