<HEADLINE> Dhaka is Becoming A Mega city </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Dhaka, the capital of
Bangladesh, is becoming a megalopolis by the turn of the century
with its population rapidly increasing to 10 million, according to
the Bangladesh Center for Advanced Studies (BCAS).
</P>
<P>
As the city is expanding rapidly, the problems in Dhaka such as
population, housing, electricity, water supply, sewage disposal,
garbage collection, transport as well as governance and finance
are mounting, BCAS's executive director Dr. Saleemul Huq said.
</P>
<P>
These problems are becoming so acute that they may choke the
city in the future, Huq told a meeting on the city's management on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
He emphasized the need for concerted efforts, involving
non-governmental organizations, the private sector, civil society,
groups and city dwellers for improving the situation.
</P>
<P>
Dhaka's growth rate of population is about six percent. More
than nine million people are living in an area of 815 square
kilometers, and the city's population density is the highest in
the world.
</P>
</TEXT>
