<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Procedures for Electing President in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's Election
Commission (EC) has announced procedures for the presidential
election underway Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Under the election law, each member of the electoral college
for casting vote in the presidential poll shall carry with him the
identity card, issued by the Secretariat of the National Assembly,
the Senate or the Secretariat of a provincial assembly.
</P>
<P>
The voting is being held in the chambers of the Parliament and
the four provincial assemblies from 10:00 a.m. to 15:00 p.m. local
time.
</P>
<P>
The electoral college of the presidential election comprises
476 voters, who are the members of the Parliament or the four
provincial assemblies.
</P>
<P>
A validly nominated candidate may, before the commencement of
the poll, appoint not more than one agent for observing the poll
and the count, and give notice thereof in writing to the presiding
officer.
</P>
<P>
The Presiding Officer, appointed by the Chief Election
Commissioner, shall regulate the entry of voters in the
alphabetical order of their names as entered in the lists of
voters so that, at a time, only one voter enters the place
reserved for making ballot papers.
</P>
<P>
The ballot papers will be counted by the Presiding Officer
immediately after the close of the poll in the presence of the
contesting candidates or their authorized representatives.
</P>
<P>
Under the election law, the Returning Officer shall count the
votes recorded for each candidate and determine the result of the
election.
</P>
<P>
After the result has been determined, the Returning Officer
shall declare the candidate who has obtained the largest number of
votes to be elected for the office of president and shall submit a
return of election to the federal government.
</P>
<P>
Where there is equality of votes amongst two or more
candidates, the selection of the candidate to be elected shall be
by drawing of lots.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
