<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesian Court Postpones Liquidation of Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, December 31 (Xinhua) -- The Jakarta State
Administrative Court Tuesday overturned decrees of the Finance
Ministry and Bank Indonesia (the central bank) to close Bank
Jakarta, and allowed the bank to remain open pending a final court
verdict on its closure.
</P>
<P>
"The ministerial decree and the central bank governor decree
have been postponed," local press reports Wednesday quoted Jakarta
State Administrative Court Chief Justice Lintong Oloan Siahaan as
saying in his preliminary verdict in the bank's case against
Finance Minister Mar'ie Muhammad and Bank Indonesia Governor
Soedrajad Djiwandono.
</P>
<P>
Bank Jakarta, owned by President Soeharto's half-brother
Probosutedjo, was one of 16 private banks liquidated by the
government on November 1 in a move to make the banking sector more
healthy.
</P>
<P>
The liquidation of 16 insolvent banks was part of reforms
ordered to comply with a 23 billion U.S. dollar aid package set up
by the International Monetary Fund (IMF) to bail out Indonesia's
ailing economy.
</P>
<P>
Bank Jakarta filed a suit contesting the rulings at the state
administrative court on November 7. Probosutedjo contended that
the decision to close his bank was unfair. His lawyer Muhammad
Yusuf said Tuesday's ruling means Bank Jakarta could "reopen its
activities right now" until a permanent decision on the suit.
</P>
<P>
However, the government lawyers did not say whether they would
appeal, but lawyer Luhut M.P. Pangaribuan said the team would file
a letter of objection to the court. He said the liquidation had
been conducted as part of the country's economic reform needed to
cope with the financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
Siahaan said the court ruling was only temporary and would
remain valid until the court decides whether or not to proceed
with the case. The next hearing was scheduled for January 8, 1998.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971231.0208 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-31 </DATE_TIME>
