<HEADLINE> Ties Sealed Between China, S. Africa Beneficial </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 31 (Xinhua) -- The establishment of
diplomatic relations between China and South Africa is of
importance and benefit to the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region (HKSAR), a Chinese diplomat said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
China and South Africa sealed diplomatic ties Tuesday when
foreign ministers of the two countries singed a joint communique
in Pretoria, South Africa.
</P>
<P>
Wu Hongbo, spokesman of the Commissioner's Office of the
Chinese Foreign Ministry in Hong Kong, told Xinhua Wednesday that
as agreed upon between the two governments, South Africa can
maintain its consulate general in the HKSAR starting from January
1, 1998.
</P>
<P>
He added that the central government has authorized the HKSAR
to negotiate with South Africa on a civil aviation agreement to
replace the current temporary arrangement.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that after China and South Africa forged diplomatic
ties, the HKSAR and South Africa will further their cooperation in
the economic, trade, shipping and tourism fields. There are broad
prospects for friendly cooperation in the future," he said.
</P>
<P>
Wu also said that the establishment of diplomatic relations
between the two countries is of great importance, and the
traditional friendship between the two peoples will develop on a
new basis.  
</P>
</TEXT>
