<HEADLINE> Remittance To Nicaragua Hit Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Remittance to Nicaragua from
Nicaraguans abroad reached an unprecedented 300-million-dollar
record in 1997, an increment of almost 50 percent over a year ago,
the local press reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The amount surpassed expectancies of the authorities, which
forecast by November just 200 million dollars, almost the same
as 1996.
</P>
<P>
It is said that the rise was due to the approval of a U.S.
migratory law that legalized the stay of 250,000 Nicaraguans in
that country, so that they can send more money home. 
</P>
</TEXT>
