<HEADLINE> Ukrainian Parliament Adopts 1998 Budget </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, December 30 (Xinhua) -- The Supreme Soviet (the Ukrainian
parliament) adopted the 1998 state budget on Tuesday after months
of debate.
</P>
<P>
The adopted budget's revenue for next year stands at 21.1
billion hryvnas (11.3 billion U.S. dollars) while the expenditure
is expected to be 24.5 billion hryvnas (13.1 Billion
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The approved revenue and expenditure includes full clearance of
back wages, which amount to nearly five billion hryvnas (2.4
billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The budget also stipulates a deficit equal to 3.3 percent of
the gross domestic product (GDP) and 13.8 percent of the budget
expenditure. The deficit is to be covered with 1.1 billion hryvnas
(588 million U.S. dollars) from internal sources and 2.3 billion
hryvnas (1.2 billion U.S. dollars) from external sources.
</P>
<P>
The budget sets the limit for domestic debts as of January 1,
1999 at 17 billion hryvnas (9 billion U.S. dollars) and the limit
for foreign debts at three billion U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
