<HEADLINE> U.S. Wrestler Convicted of Attacking Kuwaiti Anchorman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT, December 30 (Xinhua) -- An American wrestler was fined
for attacking a Kuwaiti TV anchorman on Tuesday, facing a maximum
penalty of one year imprisonment.
</P>
<P>
Leon White of Colorado, known as "Rocky Mountain Best" in the
world boxing circle, insulted Bassam al-Othman in a live interview
when the latter asked him if the matches were faked.
</P>
<P>
The wrestler was ordered to pay a 50 dinars (166 U.S. dollars)
fine, said al-Othman's lawyer Ibrahim al-Athary, adding that the
maximum penalty could have been one year in prison.
</P>
<P>
In April, White grabbed al-Othman by the tie, shoved him
backwards and shouted obscene words after being asked in the live
interview in Kuwait that if professional wrestling matches were
fake.
</P>
<P>
White's attorney Ernest Alexander said White had apologized to
al-Othman for the bad language and his behavior immediately after
the incident.
</P>
<P>
Yet, Al-Athary said al-Othman still may sue for compensation in
another court. 
</P>
</TEXT>
