<HEADLINE> Remains of US Vietnam War MIAs Found </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 30 (Xinhua) -- The remains of three
American airmen missing in the Vietnam War in 1966 and 1967 have
been found in Laos and Vietnam, the Pentagon said today.
</P>
<P>
The Pentagon said in a statement that a joint U.S.-Lao team
found the remains of Air Force Maj. Glenn Belcher, and a joint
U.S.- Vietnamese team found the remains of the other two airmen,
Maj. Ronald Sittner and 1st Lt. Brent Davis.
</P>
<P>
The Pentagon has returned the remains of the three airmen to
their families for burial.
</P>
<P>
There are still 2,099 Americans unaccounted for from the
Vietnam War. 
</P>
