<HEADLINE> U.S. Stresses Cooperation With Russia, But Also </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 30 (Xinhua) -- The United States today
said that it works closely with Russia on a wide range of global
issues, but also recognized the differences between the two world
powers.
</P>
<P>
Asked to evaluate the current U.S.-Russia relations at a
regular briefing, State Department Spokesman James Foley said
Washington and Moscow work "very closely and productively" in "all
kinds of hot spots."
</P>
<P>
However, he said, "Of course we don't always see eye to eye.
Our interests are not always the same."
</P>
<P>
Given differences in geography and history, there will be
differences in interests in given situations, said the spokesman.
"Also, there will be different views on tactics in situations
where we do agree on common objectives."
</P>
<P>
"I think that's inevitable in international relations," he
affirmed.
</P>
<P>
Russia recently expressed its concern at Washington's dominance
on world affairs, upholding building a multi-polarization world.
